    },
    {
      "_id": "09f3145e8ec30885",
      "name": "Ranged Attack",
      "sort": 7,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80da-98aa-fbbfff7ae20e\">A Ranged Attack is an Attack with a range specified in a number Spaces (such as 10 Spaces). The Range is determined by the type of Weapon it’s Attacking with or by consulting the ability used to make the Ranged Attack.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8097-84fd-cab7ade297af\"><strong>Close Quarters:</strong> You have DisADV on Ranged Attacks if you're within the Melee Range of at least 1 enemy, unless that enemy is <strong>Incapacitated</strong><strong> </strong>(see the<strong> </strong><strong>Disadvantage </strong>and <strong>Conditions </strong>sections for more information).</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8045-903c-e48ca54f3106\"><strong><span style=\"border-bottom:0.05em solid\">Weapon Ranges</span></strong></p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8036-8686-f852ec42d3b5\">A Weapon that can be used to make a Ranged Attack has a Range shown in parentheses after its Ammo, Toss, or Thrown property (see the<strong> </strong><strong>Weapons</strong> section for more information).</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80f1-9523-cce999d5ee23\"><strong>Normal Range:</strong> The first number in the parentheses is a Weapon’s normal range. You can make an attack against targets within this range. </p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-802a-b39f-dcc6493cbbc0\"><strong>Long Range:</strong> The second number in the parentheses is a Weapon’s long range. You can make an attack with DisADV against targets within this range. You can’t make attacks against targets beyond your Weapon’s long range.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80be-ba73-d2dce0ffe99d\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\"><strong>Example:</strong> A Short Bow with a range of (15/45) means that it can be used to make attacks against targets between 1 and 15 Spaces, attacks with DisADV against targets between 16 and 45 Spaces, and can’t attack targets that are 46 Spaces or farther away.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
