    {
      "_id": "0a5ab4d4445304aa",
      "name": "Area Attack",
      "sort": 8,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8044-bfb8-e4644855b249\">A creature makes an Area Attack when they make an Attack against targets that are within a specified area (such as a Cone, Line, or Sphere) covered by the Attack (see the <strong>Areas of Effects </strong>section for more information). The type and size of the area is determined by the Attack.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8003-8c64-cc7bf99a60cc\" class=\"block-color-purple_background\">DC Tip: The <strong>Close Quarters</strong> penalty doesn’t apply to Area Attacks.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
