    },
    {
      "_id": "66f68e2a863375af",
      "name": "Determining if an Attack Hits",
      "sort": 9,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-809c-8c01-ef0c170dc5d0\">When a creature makes an Attack, the result of the Attack Check is compared to the target’s Defense to determine whether or not the Attack Hits the target. The Attack Hits if the result of the Attack Check is equal to or greater than the target’s Defense.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-808a-ae9b-d8900d0146c9\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\"><strong>Example: </strong>A Level 4 Champion’s highest Attribute is a <strong>3</strong> (Prime Modifier) and their Combat Mastery is <strong>2</strong> (1/2 its level). When the Champion makes an Attack Check using a Longsword, they roll a d20 and add <strong>5</strong> (3+2). If they roll a 10 on the d20, the result is 15 (10 + 5). If the target’s PD is 15 or lower, the Attack Hits, otherwise it Misses.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 2,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
      "system": {},
      "image": {},
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
      "category": null,
      "flags": {},
      "_stats": {
